CooL produces and verifies evidentiary records of what an AI system computed
(which model, on which input, producing which output, and when) and proves that
such records are unforged. It does NOT prove that any output is correct, fair,
unbiased, safe, or policy-compliant. See cool-spec/STATUS.md for the honest,
per-domain implementation status (TEE attestation is mocked and on-chain
anchoring is not present in v0.1.0).
